import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region')['total'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['region'], data['total'])
    plt.title('What is the average income for each region?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['pct'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['pct'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['pct'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income percentages across all regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='pct', by='group', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Income Group')
    ax.set_ylabel('Percentage of Income')
    ax.set_title('How does the income distribution vary across income groups?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    regions = data['region'].unique()
    colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'purple']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for i, region in enumerate(regions):
        region_data = data[data['region'] == region]
        ax.scatter(region_data['region'], region_data['total'], color=colors[i], label=region)
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Total Income')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between income and region?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    income_group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    labels = income_group_counts.index.tolist()
    sizes = income_group_counts.values.tolist()
    fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax1.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax1.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the most common income group across all regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
